00:14:32.760 --> 00:14:36.196
I'm just saying,
she's cluttering up the TiVo.

00:14:36.360 --> 00:14:38.874
And a clear TiVo equals a clear mind.

00:14:40.280 --> 00:14:42.874
Are we okay with the kids going
to that concert?

00:14:43.040 --> 00:14:45.600
- Yeah.
- What if Rooney is, like...

00:14:45.760 --> 00:14:49.150
...death-metal Satan-worshipping
speed freaks?

00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:52.039
Honey, that went out in the late '90s.

00:14:53.040 --> 00:14:55.156
I saw it on a special on E!

00:14:55.320 --> 00:14:59.074
I'll run Rooney up my proverbial flagpole,
but you have got to speak to Hailey.

00:15:02.960 --> 00:15:04.234
So?

00:15:04.400 --> 00:15:09.758
- Yeah, it's my first time hearing it, so...
- That's why we're doing a run-through.

00:15:09.920 --> 00:15:12.673
- So you'll have heard it all before tonight.
- Right.

00:15:12.840 --> 00:15:15.195
- So we're going tonight?
- No. It's your first concert.

00:15:15.360 --> 00:15:18.591
We have free tickets, backstage passes.
You're right, we should skip it.

00:15:18.760 --> 00:15:22.150
- That's not what I'm saying.
- What are you saying?

00:15:23.240 --> 00:15:26.391
- Have you met Natalie?
- No, but I hear she's great.

00:15:26.560 --> 00:15:29.996
- And Oliver is...? I mean...
- Is someone jealous?

00:15:31.880 --> 00:15:36.874
This song is good.
Turn it up. Really, really loud.

00:15:44.640 --> 00:15:49.509
Oliver will be with Natalie.
Rooney is a really good band.

00:15:49.680 --> 00:15:52.592
- And tonight we're gonna have fun.
- I know.

00:15:52.760 --> 00:15:56.799
- There won't be dancing, right?
- I'll dance. You can watch.

00:15:56.960 --> 00:15:58.996
Works for me.

00:16:10.080 --> 00:16:11.593
- I think that's enough.
- What?

00:16:11.760 --> 00:16:14.194
There was almost a knee bend.
You were about to find the beat.

00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:17.318
- And?
- Remember cousin Jeffery's bar mitzvah?

00:16:17.480 --> 00:16:19.869
You almost wiped out a dozen kids
on the dance floor.

00:16:20.040 --> 00:16:22.554
That "Y.M.C.A." song
requires a lot of movement.

00:16:22.720 --> 00:16:26.713
- I'm just trying to spare casualties.
- So anyone gonna be doing drugs?

00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:28.950
I hope so, otherwise
it's a lame-ass concert.

00:16:29.120 --> 00:16:30.997
Anyone named Seth
gonna be doing any drugs?

00:16:31.160 --> 00:16:33.628
No. Nobody named Seth Cohen.
I promise.

00:16:33.800 --> 00:16:36.075
Gotta stay sharp.
It's my first date with Anna.

00:16:36.240 --> 00:16:39.357
It is? So you and Summer
finally had the talk?

00:16:39.520 --> 00:16:41.476
Oh, yes, almost several times.

00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:43.153
- Seth.
- Father.

00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:46.198
The sooner you tell her,
the better you'll feel about everything.

00:16:46.360 --> 00:16:48.112
See, I don't really believe that.

00:16:48.280 --> 00:16:52.671
I'm feeling like the longer I wait
to tell her, the longer I'll feel great.

00:16:52.840 --> 00:16:54.751
The best advice
I can give you is this.

00:16:54.920 --> 00:16:57.753
It's from Steven Seagal in
his classic film <i>Hard to Kill.</i>

00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:02.150
"The anticipation of death
is far worse than death itself."

00:17:02.320 --> 00:17:05.232
Great. So then we both agree
that Summer's gonna kill me.

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:08.039
Look, if you're old enough
to go to a concert alone...

00:17:08.200 --> 00:17:10.953
...if you're old enough to embark
on a real relationship...

00:17:11.120 --> 00:17:13.475
...you are old enough to be a man.

00:17:15.240 --> 00:17:18.835
Well, she's not gonna be
there tonight...

00:17:19.000 --> 00:17:20.797
...so I'll tell her Monday.
- Good.

00:17:21.600 --> 00:17:24.717
Now, get going. Your mother
and I want some time alone.

00:17:25.120 --> 00:17:27.839
There's a visual that
I don't want to take with me tonight.

00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:30.798
Well, son, your mom's a hottie,
and I got her.

00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:40.996
- I don't see him.
- Maybe he's inside.

00:17:42.920 --> 00:17:45.878
- Excuse me, are you on the list?
- Yeah, we're with Oliver Trask.

00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:48.270
- Who's Oliver Trask?
- You don't have his name?

00:17:48.440 --> 00:17:52.797
No, I don't have his name.
I've never heard it. That's why I'm asking.

00:17:52.960 --> 00:17:56.953
- Thanks, you've been very helpful.
- I'll call him and see where he is.

00:17:57.120 --> 00:17:59.395
- A lot of freaks here, huh, Cohen?
- Yeah.

00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:02.757
Good job, Luke. That should
help make us a lot of friends.

00:18:02.920 --> 00:18:04.353
- Damn it.
- What?

00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:08.513
Well, dude, they're gonna go on soon.
If Oliver's late, we'll miss the first song.

00:18:08.680 --> 00:18:12.639
They only have one album. Factor in
your standard cover, that's 12 songs.

00:18:12.800 --> 00:18:15.155
Oh, no. But, hey. I mean, come on.

00:18:15.320 --> 00:18:18.312
If we don't get in,
we're still gonna have fun tonight.

00:18:18.480 --> 00:18:20.152
- Right?
- What are we gonna do?

00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:23.319
I hope you guys aren't waiting for me.

00:18:24.560 --> 00:18:26.471
- Summer.
- Cohen.

00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:29.234
- Hey, Anna.
- Summer.

00:18:31.120 --> 00:18:33.918
- Who are you talking to?
- It just goes straight to voice mail.

00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:36.548
Dude, look at that freak.

00:18:36.720 --> 00:18:38.551
Hey, I drove alone.
Will you ride with me?

00:18:38.720 --> 00:18:41.757
You want to give up so early?
Maybe I can grease a few palms.

00:18:41.920 --> 00:18:43.638
Hey.

00:18:44.600 --> 00:18:46.556
- There you are.
- What's up, man?

00:18:46.720 --> 00:18:49.393
- Hi.
- I thought you were a no-show.

00:18:49.560 --> 00:18:52.757
- What happened? I said back door.
- No, you didn't.

00:18:52.920 --> 00:18:56.151
- Load in here, guys.
- The band's here.

00:18:56.320 --> 00:18:57.753
- It's all happening.
- What up, guys?

00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:00.753
Robert, how's it going?
Good to see you.

00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:02.319
Looking forward to the show.

00:19:02.480 --> 00:19:05.233
- Thank you.
- I guess we're on time.

00:19:05.400 --> 00:19:07.960
- Which one's Rooney?
- They're all Rooney.

00:19:08.120 --> 00:19:11.669
- Hey, man, this is my posse.
- This is crazy.

00:19:12.400 --> 00:19:16.837
- Hey. So where's Natalie?
- Yeah, we had another fight.

00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:21.152
This whole long-distance thing's tough.
Looks like I'm dateless tonight.

00:19:21.320 --> 00:19:24.278
Hey, no! No way.
We'll be your date, right?

00:19:24.960 --> 00:19:26.234
Yeah, right.

00:19:26.400 --> 00:19:30.916
- So should we fire up the hot tub?
- Interesting. Open a bottle of wine.

00:19:31.080 --> 00:19:33.150
Oh, I like it.

00:19:33.320 --> 00:19:35.356
First, TiVo. I'm gonna
erase Hailey's programs.

00:19:35.520 --> 00:19:36.999
- Hot pizza?
- Hailey.

00:19:37.160 --> 00:19:39.435
Hey, guys. You're just in time.

00:19:40.320 --> 00:19:42.629
Doctor. Doctor.

00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:46.073
- James.
- What's up?

00:19:47.240 --> 00:19:49.595
I just thought that you were
going out tonight.

00:19:49.760 --> 00:19:53.514
We were. But then I found out there's
a <i>Golden Girls</i> marathon on Lifetime.

00:19:53.680 --> 00:19:56.114
And I decided to dig up
all my favorite board games.

00:19:56.280 --> 00:19:58.840
We're having a throwback
to the old babysitting days.

00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:03.232
- Why don't you guys join us?
- Great. That would be great.

00:20:04.040 --> 00:20:07.476
Oh, I love this episode. This is the one
where Rose adopts the pig.

00:20:07.640 --> 00:20:09.039
She adopted the pig?

00:20:18.040 --> 00:20:20.679
- Do you play?
- A little.

00:20:20.840 --> 00:20:23.115
- Here, man.
- All access? Sweet.

00:20:24.520 --> 00:20:27.080
- Hey, it's cool?
- It's cool.

00:20:27.240 --> 00:20:29.037
- Hey, check it out.
- Seriously?

00:20:29.200 --> 00:20:30.997
Yeah.

00:20:31.160 --> 00:20:35.790
Awesome.
I just got a few songs that I wrote.

00:20:44.520 --> 00:20:47.398
Okay, I'm just gonna...

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:50.515
Seth, you have to tell her tonight.

00:20:50.680 --> 00:20:53.114
- No, I don't.
- Hey.

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:54.633
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

00:20:54.800 --> 00:20:57.109
- So, Luke, he's...
- Yeah, we don't let him out much.

00:21:01.200 --> 00:21:03.430
Yeah. But you guys are cool,
having fun?

00:21:03.600 --> 00:21:05.511
- Everything's awesome.
- Glad to hear it.

00:21:05.680 --> 00:21:07.989
Yeah. Everything is not awesome.

00:21:08.160 --> 00:21:11.072
If I don't tell Summer tonight,
then later, when I do tell her...

00:21:11.240 --> 00:21:14.232
...she'll remember the fun she had
at Rooney. That will cheer her up.

00:21:14.400 --> 00:21:18.712
There's never gonna be a good time
to tell her. Tonight's not a bad night.

00:21:18.880 --> 00:21:23.476
There's a lot of guys here.
Cute guys, older guys. A lot of musicians.

00:21:23.640 --> 00:21:25.790
Girls like musicians.

00:21:25.960 --> 00:21:28.190
Maybe you're right.

00:21:28.840 --> 00:21:31.832
Am I flattering myself
to even think that Summer'll care?

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:36.516
I mean, me compared
to that dude or that guy.

00:21:36.680 --> 00:21:38.511
- Right.
- Are you checking out dudes again?

00:21:39.080 --> 00:21:40.638
No.

00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:44.349
But there are plenty here tonight,
aren't there? A lot of musicians.

00:21:44.520 --> 00:21:46.909
In fact, I think I'm gonna go
find some myself.

00:21:47.080 --> 00:21:50.959
Why don't you and Seth talk.
You know, about anything.

00:21:52.160 --> 00:21:56.836
- Cohen, you and Anna...?
- Me and Anna what? What?

00:21:58.080 --> 00:22:00.196
Will you guys stand with me
at the concert?

00:22:00.360 --> 00:22:02.920
Marissa's on a date,
and I'm all alone tonight, so...

00:22:03.080 --> 00:22:04.354
Okay, that would be nice.

00:22:13.280 --> 00:22:17.512
Yeah. Hey, man. I thought your boy
was supposed to be here an hour ago.

00:22:17.680 --> 00:22:19.591
No. Okay, no excuses.

00:22:19.760 --> 00:22:24.515
I don't care who you send. Just make
sure it's good and it gets here quick.

00:22:24.680 --> 00:22:26.432
All right.

00:22:38.080 --> 00:22:42.039
I can't see. I'm stuck behind
a row of giants. Come with me.

00:22:42.200 --> 00:22:43.633
Okay, lead the way.

00:22:48.040 --> 00:22:50.235
Sorry.

00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:55.878
Hey. Did you tell her?
What did she say? Did she leave?

00:22:56.040 --> 00:22:58.270
No. Summer is bringing refreshments
for her friends.

00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:02.353
- Seth said you were thirsty.
- Yeah. You are thirsty, aren't you?

00:23:04.280 --> 00:23:05.793
- <i>You suck.</i>
- <i>I'm sorry.</i>

00:23:07.000 --> 00:23:10.754
- I gotta pee. You gotta pee?
- I'll come with you.

00:23:11.120 --> 00:23:12.314
<i>I'm telling her.</i>

00:23:18.200 --> 00:23:21.988
You know the night that Mom and Dad
came home early from Palm Springs?

00:23:22.160 --> 00:23:24.276
And we flushed all that beer
down the toilet.

00:23:24.440 --> 00:23:26.032
- A lot of good that did.
- I know.

00:23:26.200 --> 00:23:28.191
Dad caught you
throwing out the empty bottles.

00:23:28.600 --> 00:23:30.795
- I thought you were sleeping.
- Face it, sister.

00:23:30.960 --> 00:23:32.632
Everything I know,
I learned from you.

00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:34.552
You were a bad influence
back in the day.

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:36.836
How do you think I learned
to piss off Dad?

00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:40.595
- The student becomes the master.
- And the master becomes Dad's slave.

00:23:40.760 --> 00:23:45.276
Helping to turn paradise into a parking lot,
or at least a three-car garage.

00:23:48.080 --> 00:23:50.435
Hey, Connect Four!

00:23:50.600 --> 00:23:52.955
Congratulations.
Next Saturday, Yahtzee.

00:23:53.120 --> 00:23:55.918
No, wait. Stay. Battleship? Uno?

00:23:56.080 --> 00:23:57.991
You know, Sandy's right. It's late.

00:23:58.160 --> 00:24:01.391
And, besides, I have a show home
waiting for me in the morning.

00:24:01.560 --> 00:24:04.199
Just what Orange County needs.
Another show home.

00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:07.511
Airlifted from the McMansion factory
and dropped from the sky...

00:24:07.680 --> 00:24:10.240
The one on the bluff,
that's a great house.

00:24:10.400 --> 00:24:14.837
If by "great" you mean overbuilt,
overpriced and exactly like this one.

00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:18.117
- Oh, nice. Hailey, nice.
- I was kidding.

00:24:18.280 --> 00:24:21.511
- I'm laughing on the inside.
- I'm not. You're living in our home.

00:24:21.680 --> 00:24:25.958
You're insulting my wife.
You're driving my whole family crazy.

00:24:26.120 --> 00:24:27.951
- Is this true?
- Yeah.

00:24:28.120 --> 00:24:30.156
And we all know
what you're doing here.

00:24:32.400 --> 00:24:35.119
She didn't mean anything.
It's just sisters.

00:24:35.280 --> 00:24:38.238
No, all this talk about plans,
about growing up, it's shtick.

00:24:38.400 --> 00:24:41.119
It's a routine. And it's tired.

00:24:41.280 --> 00:24:43.396
You know who's tired? Me.
So why don't we stop.

00:24:43.560 --> 00:24:44.834
No, stop protecting her.

00:24:45.280 --> 00:24:48.556
You're not even nice to Kirsten.
She's the only reason we put up with you.

00:24:48.720 --> 00:24:52.998
Well, you won't have to put up with me
for much longer, okay?

00:25:01.240 --> 00:25:03.276
- Sorry?
- It's not your fault, Jimmy.

00:25:03.440 --> 00:25:05.351
No, I meant the board game.

00:25:20.840 --> 00:25:22.592
- You like <i>The Golden Girls</i>?
- Yes.

00:25:22.760 --> 00:25:25.638
There's a marathon on.
I can't get the song out of my head.

00:25:25.800 --> 00:25:27.358
I love <i>The Golden Girls.</i>

00:25:27.520 --> 00:25:29.670
It's not Rose's fault.
She just is that way.

00:25:29.840 --> 00:25:31.876
You're Rose? I'm Blanche.

00:25:32.040 --> 00:25:34.918
It's kind of weird that I relate
to a 70-year-old, but...

00:25:35.080 --> 00:25:37.594
How good was the episode
when there was a blackout?

00:25:37.760 --> 00:25:39.830
How about when Rose adopts the pig?

00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:43.993
Then Sophia loses her glasses
and thinks the pig is a baby.

00:25:44.160 --> 00:25:45.957
It's so funny.

00:25:56.600 --> 00:25:59.239
Jimmy, wait.

00:25:59.480 --> 00:26:03.393
Sorry about that in there.
My little tantrum.

00:26:03.560 --> 00:26:08.918
Oh, listen, it's complicated between
you and your sister. It always has been.

00:26:09.080 --> 00:26:11.116
You gotta go, like, right now?

00:26:11.280 --> 00:26:15.159
Yeah, I don't know if I ever told you,
but I'm an extremely important person.

00:26:15.320 --> 00:26:18.118
And so I have to...

00:26:18.520 --> 00:26:21.956
Yeah. No, Marissa's at a concert.

00:26:23.120 --> 00:26:25.270
Yep, nothing but time.

00:26:26.000 --> 00:26:28.036
Didn't tonight feel like
the good old days?

00:26:28.920 --> 00:26:34.711
No. It was more like two kind of pathetic
people grasping for the old days.

00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:38.470
- Right. That too.
- Yeah.

00:26:38.640 --> 00:26:41.916
Look, the good old days.
They're exactly that.

00:26:42.080 --> 00:26:45.595
Would you really want to be back
in high school?

00:26:46.960 --> 00:26:48.518
- Yeah.
- Yeah. I would too.

00:26:49.240 --> 00:26:55.315
- And you think I'm pathetic?
- Yes, I do. It's sad, really.

00:27:10.640 --> 00:27:12.915
I always had a crush on you.
You know that?

00:27:13.360 --> 00:27:17.194
No. You were 8
when I went away to college.

00:27:17.360 --> 00:27:19.590
So I wasn't...

00:27:24.160 --> 00:27:27.755
You're Kirsten's sister.

00:27:28.560 --> 00:27:30.312
So I've heard all my life.

00:27:30.840 --> 00:27:33.434
Look, we don't want to make
a complicated situation...

00:27:33.600 --> 00:27:35.556
...even more complicated, right?

00:27:35.920 --> 00:27:40.789
The last thing we need is having
Sandy or Kirsten catching us.

00:27:40.960 --> 00:27:43.793
Unless that's what you're hoping for.

00:27:46.040 --> 00:27:49.271
Look, your sister is amazing...

00:27:49.440 --> 00:27:52.637
...and Sandy is such a great guy.

00:27:52.800 --> 00:27:55.872
I think you're lucky
to have them looking out for you.

00:27:56.760 --> 00:27:58.876
I know that I am.

00:28:02.560 --> 00:28:04.312
I'm gonna go.

00:28:04.480 --> 00:28:06.357
Okay.

00:29:30.880 --> 00:29:33.440
- Hi. I'm gonna...
- Hey, this is great, right?

00:29:33.600 --> 00:29:35.352
Perfect.

00:29:36.400 --> 00:29:38.834
Come here a second.

00:29:59.160 --> 00:30:01.151
- What are we doing?
- This is better.

00:30:01.320 --> 00:30:04.392
Wait. But we're missing the concert.
We can't ditch Oliver.

00:30:04.560 --> 00:30:08.155
- Oliver's fine. He's friends with the band.
- And with us.

00:30:08.320 --> 00:30:10.959
I thought you said you wanted us
to hang out with friends.

00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:14.351
You've known him two weeks.
How good a friend can he be?

00:30:14.520 --> 00:30:17.034
Look. He's in recovery,
trying to stay clean.

00:30:17.200 --> 00:30:18.713
We can talk about stuff.

00:30:18.880 --> 00:30:21.235
He tells me things.
What he's going through.

00:30:21.400 --> 00:30:23.960
- Unlike me, right?
- I didn't say that.

00:30:28.320 --> 00:30:30.356
I know you didn't want
to come here tonight...

00:30:30.520 --> 00:30:32.750
...so, I mean,
I guess if you want to leave...

00:30:34.120 --> 00:30:35.599
Right.

00:30:36.440 --> 00:30:38.032
Later.

00:30:48.280 --> 00:30:50.236
Hey, Luke.

00:30:50.400 --> 00:30:53.233
- You know who sings this song?
- Rooney.

00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:56.639
- Rooney!
- We should keep it that way.

00:30:56.800 --> 00:30:58.870
Yeah, Rooney!

00:31:10.120 --> 00:31:11.917
What the hell, man?! Get off me!

00:31:14.760 --> 00:31:18.196
- Hey, get off him!
- I'm a cop.

00:31:18.960 --> 00:31:22.032
- What? There's gotta be some mistake.
- Yeah. His.

00:31:22.200 --> 00:31:24.634
He just tried to buy
3 grams of coke from me.

00:31:26.120 --> 00:31:28.998
Ryan, go back inside.
Don't tell anybody.

00:32:08.240 --> 00:32:12.074
Excuse me, barkeep, sir.

00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:15.355
- Hey.
- What can I get you?

00:32:15.920 --> 00:32:19.549
How did you do that? The usual.

00:32:19.760 --> 00:32:21.193
- Mountain Dew.
- How many?

00:32:22.440 --> 00:32:24.396
Unfortunately, three.

00:32:24.560 --> 00:32:26.710
So Anna's telling Summer
that we're a couple.

00:32:26.880 --> 00:32:30.156
When they get back, I will officially
be in a relationship with Anna.

00:32:30.320 --> 00:32:32.914
Unless Summer kills me,
in which case, you've been like a brother.

00:32:33.080 --> 00:32:34.798
Good, because I need
your keys and phone.

00:32:34.960 --> 00:32:37.918
- Yeah, you okay?
- I'm fine. It's Oliver.

00:32:38.320 --> 00:32:41.551
- What? What's going on?
- Tell you later?

00:32:41.720 --> 00:32:43.870
All right. You'll miss
a hell of a show, though.

00:32:44.040 --> 00:32:46.190
Rooney's not bad, either.

00:32:49.280 --> 00:32:52.556
- Is Jimmy gone?
- Yeah. Is she all right?

00:32:52.720 --> 00:32:54.950
I knocked. She didn't answer.

00:32:55.120 --> 00:32:56.872
Maybe she's giving us the house back.

00:32:57.040 --> 00:33:01.033
Or maybe she's packing and she'll
be gone in the morning. And frankly...

00:33:01.200 --> 00:33:05.113
...I'd rather have her here, where I can
keep an eye on her, than anywhere else.

00:33:05.280 --> 00:33:10.308
You can't keep her here forever. It's no
good for her and it's no good for us.

00:33:11.080 --> 00:33:12.399
Hello?

00:33:13.520 --> 00:33:15.636
Hey, what's wrong?

00:33:15.880 --> 00:33:18.155
Where are you?

00:33:18.760 --> 00:33:20.239
I'll be right there.

00:33:20.400 --> 00:33:22.960
Ryan's at the police station.

00:33:30.720 --> 00:33:33.518
Thank you, Newport Beach.
Good night, everybody.

00:33:41.200 --> 00:33:42.997
- Seth.
- Hey.

00:33:43.160 --> 00:33:45.276
- Where have you been?
- At the bar. How was it?

00:33:45.440 --> 00:33:47.590
It was amazing.
They played the whole album.

00:33:47.760 --> 00:33:50.638
Not with Rooney, how did it go
with Summer? Did you tell her?

00:33:50.800 --> 00:33:52.916
Tell me what?

00:33:59.360 --> 00:34:00.634
So you're a couple?

00:34:00.800 --> 00:34:02.313
- No.
- Yes.

00:34:02.480 --> 00:34:06.678
We wanted to tell you first before we
became a couple, which now we are.

00:34:06.840 --> 00:34:08.751
- So you chose Anna?
- No.

00:34:09.000 --> 00:34:12.231
Kind of, yeah.
She came over on New Year's Eve.

00:34:12.400 --> 00:34:14.277
You were with me on New Year's Eve.

00:34:14.440 --> 00:34:17.591
Technically, you were with
that guy Allan, remember?

00:34:17.760 --> 00:34:22.151
And you kept insisting that
I go find someone to kiss, so I did.

00:34:22.320 --> 00:34:25.869
I was taking out the garbage, she was
in the driveway. You know how it goes.

00:34:26.040 --> 00:34:28.713
Okay, well, congrats.

00:34:30.640 --> 00:34:32.710
You're not mad?

00:34:35.200 --> 00:34:38.397
Good, because I didn't want this
to affect our relationship in any way.

00:34:38.560 --> 00:34:41.199
Well, Anna, I have to say...

00:34:41.360 --> 00:34:45.194
...that Rose would've never pulled
that New Year's stunt on Blanche.

00:34:45.360 --> 00:34:47.157
I know. I'm sorry.

00:34:47.320 --> 00:34:50.551
Although Blanche
would've done it to Rose, so...

00:34:51.640 --> 00:34:54.791
So can we still all hang out?
Will you be cool with that?

00:34:54.960 --> 00:34:57.872
We'd both really like that
if we could hang out.

00:34:59.440 --> 00:35:03.274
Sure. You guys,
we can totally hang out.

00:35:03.440 --> 00:35:06.557
I mean, in fact,
what are you guys doing right now?

00:35:16.520 --> 00:35:19.159
So they're gonna let him go.

00:35:19.320 --> 00:35:22.118
- Really? How'd you do that?
- I'm just that good.

00:35:22.280 --> 00:35:25.875
- I used to play poker with these guys.
- Thanks for doing this.

00:35:26.040 --> 00:35:28.713
- You didn't have to, really.
- Is this kid a friend of yours?

00:35:28.880 --> 00:35:30.313
He's a friend of Marissa's.

00:35:30.480 --> 00:35:33.199
They met in therapy.
He said he's been clean a while, but...

00:35:33.360 --> 00:35:34.873
They busted him trying to buy coke.

00:35:35.040 --> 00:35:38.271
Then he said his parents are away
for a month. Can you believe that?

00:35:38.440 --> 00:35:40.158
A parent leaves a kid
like that on his own.

00:35:40.320 --> 00:35:41.992
Yeah, imagine that.

00:35:43.320 --> 00:35:45.675
- I'll never understand it.
- I hope not.

00:35:47.440 --> 00:35:50.671
- I'm glad you called me.
- Me too.

00:35:57.440 --> 00:36:01.319
I'm gonna finish up your paperwork.
You sit tight. I'll be right back.

00:36:07.080 --> 00:36:09.958
So thanks.

00:36:10.680 --> 00:36:12.910
Seth's dad seems cool.

00:36:13.880 --> 00:36:15.871
He is.

00:36:17.320 --> 00:36:19.914
So why'd you do this for me?

00:36:20.440 --> 00:36:22.954
I mean, you don't even like me, man.

00:36:23.720 --> 00:36:25.790
I don't really know you.

00:36:26.840 --> 00:36:32.517
Well, if it's any consolation, I don't
like myself very much right now, either.

00:36:37.560 --> 00:36:41.314
- So, what happened?
- I don't know.

00:36:41.480 --> 00:36:46.156
Natalie didn't show.
And then I saw you and Marissa.

00:36:46.760 --> 00:36:48.876
Your friends.

00:36:49.800 --> 00:36:51.358
Then it hit me.

00:36:51.520 --> 00:36:55.354
I have no one. My parents are gone.

00:36:55.520 --> 00:36:59.911
My friends,
if you can even call them that...

00:37:00.080 --> 00:37:02.719
...they all disappeared
when I got clean.

00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:04.791
Now I...

00:37:10.120 --> 00:37:13.999
There's Marissa.
Seth likes your taste in music.

00:37:14.840 --> 00:37:17.354
And Luke pretty much
likes everybody at this point.

00:37:20.040 --> 00:37:24.397
And what about you? I mean, you must
like me a little to get me out of jail.

00:37:24.600 --> 00:37:27.273
No, that was Sandy.

00:37:36.360 --> 00:37:38.157
Marissa.

00:37:38.800 --> 00:37:40.472
You gonna tell her?

00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:42.831
No.

00:37:43.280 --> 00:37:44.952
You are.

00:37:52.640 --> 00:37:54.437
Hey.

00:37:54.880 --> 00:37:56.950
Yeah, it's Oliver.

00:38:11.600 --> 00:38:13.955
Hey, whoa, hey, hey, hey!

00:38:14.120 --> 00:38:16.634
- I can't have half?
- There are other bagels.

00:38:16.800 --> 00:38:20.554
- Not salt bagels.
- You ate them all. And several sesame.

00:38:21.880 --> 00:38:24.519
I haven't been the best guest, I know.

00:38:25.280 --> 00:38:29.876
- And what you said tonight...
- Hey, Connect Four was happening.

00:38:30.040 --> 00:38:32.270
It gets my blood up.

00:38:32.440 --> 00:38:34.556
Well, you were right.

00:38:37.360 --> 00:38:42.639
So, what's the plan? Hit Caleb up
for more cash. And then what?

00:38:42.800 --> 00:38:47.271
- Europe this time? Iceland? Boca?
- I don't know.

00:38:48.200 --> 00:38:52.352
You know, I see how happy you guys are,
and I think, "Why can't I have that?"

00:38:52.520 --> 00:38:54.829
- Because you don't want it.
- How do you know?

00:38:55.000 --> 00:38:57.514
I don't even know what I want.

00:38:58.760 --> 00:39:00.751
You could stay here.

00:39:00.920 --> 00:39:03.275
I mean, not here exactly...

00:39:03.520 --> 00:39:05.829
...but, you know, get a home.

00:39:07.640 --> 00:39:11.872
- A job. Settle down.
- No.

00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:16.834
See, that's the thing.
All I know is what I don't want.

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:21.039
Well, that's not entirely true.

00:39:24.360 --> 00:39:26.237
And the rest...

00:39:26.640 --> 00:39:29.677
...you'll figure out. Good night.

00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:31.878
Good night.

00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:44.070
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:39:44.760 --> 00:39:46.671
No, wait, don't get up.

00:39:55.080 --> 00:39:56.752
Thanks.

00:39:58.240 --> 00:39:59.912
He's not a bad guy, Oliver. He's...

00:40:00.080 --> 00:40:01.433
This may come as a shock to you...

00:40:01.600 --> 00:40:04.831
...but right now,
I don't want to talk about Oliver.

00:40:12.280 --> 00:40:15.033
Oh, hey, wow, kissing.
Sorry about that.

00:40:15.200 --> 00:40:18.476
We're gonna hang out inside, but
you guys are obviously alone together...

00:40:18.640 --> 00:40:19.675
...so do that.

00:40:19.840 --> 00:40:22.798
- Ryan, what happened to you?
- Luke, please, you're shouting.

00:40:22.960 --> 00:40:27.112
- Someone stood too close to the speaker.
- Dude, that concert did not suck at all.

00:40:27.280 --> 00:40:32.070
- We PlayStationing it, or what?
- Yeah. Any time you want to join us.

00:40:32.240 --> 00:40:34.515
Let's go before he wakes up
your parents.

00:40:34.680 --> 00:40:36.352
Think we can teach him to fetch?

00:40:36.520 --> 00:40:40.559
I don't want to be the third wheel
or watch you guys make out, so enjoy.

00:40:42.360 --> 00:40:46.353
- Well, we could stay here.
- Yeah, but maybe we should...

00:40:47.040 --> 00:40:48.871
Race you?

00:40:49.640 --> 00:40:51.790
Cohen, you've played
this game before?

00:40:51.960 --> 00:40:54.520
See the way I ripped
that guy's spine out?

00:40:54.680 --> 00:40:56.750
Sitting right here, buddy.

00:40:58.720 --> 00:41:03.430
I am so glad we all could hang out
together like this, aren't you guys?

00:41:04.720 --> 00:41:05.914
- Yeah.
- Damn it.

00:41:06.080 --> 00:41:07.593
- Ryan, you're up.
- You're up, Ryan.

00:41:07.760 --> 00:41:10.115
We'll make it best of five.

00:00:0.500 --> 00:00:2.00
